<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-001-291 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 641 376</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Dec 16 1991 v8 n50 p33(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Word for OS/2 upgrade postponed; with few users, unknownprospects, Microsoft bides time. (Microsoft Corp.'s Word for OS/2word processing software, OS/2 operating system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rooney, Paula.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp decides not to produce an upgrade for its Word forOS/2 word processing software.andP;  Instead, the software publisher isreleasing a minor maintenance release that includes bug fixes andadditional graphics and word-processor filters.andP;  The originalversion of Word for OS/2 features strengths of the Word forWindows version, but lacks support of special capabilities thatthe OS/2 operating system has, including its 32-bit call feature.andO;Users also complain of substandard technical support.andP;  The growingconfrontation between Microsoft and IBM, which supports the OS/2operating system, is beginning to make users feel caught inbetween the two software publishers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Product development).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Word for OS-2 (Word processing software) (Productdevelopment)OS/2 (Operating system) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentWord processing software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>